63
00:02:22.190 --> 00:02:24.325
refer to how the
firewall operates.

64
00:02:24.325 --> 00:02:26.450
Stateful refers to a class

65
00:02:26.450 --> 00:02:27.680
of firewall that keeps track of

66
00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:29.195
information passing through it

67
00:02:29.195 --> 00:02:31.565
and proactively
filters out threats.

68
00:02:31.565 --> 00:02:33.470
A stateful firewall analyzes

69
00:02:33.470 --> 00:02:35.090
network traffic for
characteristics and

70
00:02:35.090 --> 00:02:37.280
behavior that appear suspicious

71
00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:39.365
and stops them from
entering the network.

72
00:02:39.365 --> 00:02:41.630
Stateless refers to a class

73
00:02:41.630 --> 00:02:43.040
of firewall that
operates based on

74
00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:44.870
predefined rules and does not

75
00:02:44.870 --> 00:02:47.075
keep track of information
from data packets.

76
00:02:47.075 --> 00:02:49.940
A stateless firewall
only acts according to

77
00:02:49.940 --> 00:02:52.910
preconfigured rules set by
the firewall administrator.

78
00:02:52.910 --> 00:02:55.700
The rules programmed by the
firewall administrator tell

79
00:02:55.700 --> 00:02:58.535
the device what to accept
and what to reject.

80
00:02:58.535 --> 00:03:01.775
A stateless firewall doesn't
store analyzed information.

81
00:03:01.775 --> 00:03:03.230
It also doesn't discover

82
00:03:03.230 --> 00:03:05.915
suspicious trends like a
stateful firewall does.

83
00:03:05.915 --> 00:03:08.510
For this reason, stateless
firewalls are considered

84
00:03:08.510 --> 00:03:11.060
less secure than
stateful firewalls.

85
